<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Meeting Views Peace, Jihadi Formations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2501195594 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 25 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2501195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Pashto </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A cabinet meeting was chaired this morning by 
esteemed Mawlawi Arsalan Rahmani, the deputy prime minister 
[name and titled as received]. 
  The press department of the prime minister's office told a 
Bakhtar Information Agency correspondent that various political, 
social, and economic topics were discussed in today's meeting 
and necessary measures were taken. 
  Also, an appointed cabinet delegation, including Hojjat 
ol-Eslam Seyyed Mohammad 'Ali Javid, the minister of planning, 
esteemed engineer Bashir, the acting minister of foodstuffs and 
light industries [name and title as received], esteemed Seyyed 
Mohammad Ayub, the minister of water and power [name and titled 
as received], esteemed Abdol Hay Elahi, the minister advisor to 
the Islamic State, and Gholam Sakhi Mesbah, the deputy minister 
of information and culture [name and title as received] -- that 
had been appointed to bring about reconciliation, peace, and 
understanding between Jihadi formations -- presented their work 
report to the Cabinet meeting. After assessing the report, the 
cabinet approved the following points: 
  1. The present problems between Jihadi formations should be 
solved thorough talks. 
  2. All sides should try [words indistinct] toward the 
election of the future leadership in [words indistinct] six 
months. 
  3. The Cabinet delegation is ready to declare a cease-fire 
between the state and Hezb-e Eslami [Islamic Party of 
Afghanistan] very soon through delegations of goodwill. 

</TEXT>

